    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-07-14T22:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-07-14T22:36:00-05:00" n="135"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <head>135. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Lebanon</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d135fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 783A.00/7–1458. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>.
                        Drafted by <persName>Symmes</persName> and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RSW1">Rockwell</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RWM1"
                            >Rountree</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RGF1">Reinhardt</persName>,
                        and with <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>. Also sent to London and
                        repeated to <gloss target="#t_CINCNELM1">CINCNELM</gloss>, COMSIXTH FLEET,
                            <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-07-14T23:36:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1958—11:36 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>204. London for <persName corresp="#p_BW2">Barbour</persName>. Deptel 189.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d135fn2">See <ref target="#d124fn3">footnote 3, Document
                            124</ref>.</note> President has issued orders for amphibious landing by
                    Marine battalion landing team at Beirut 1500 Beirut time tomorrow July fifteen.
                    No later than noon (that is at least three hours prior landing) you should
                    therefore inform <persName corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName> that foregoing
                    action being taken pursuant his request and that US Government expects full
                    cooperation Lebanese armed forces. In so informing <persName corresp="#p_CC7"
                        >Chamoun</persName> you should at your discretion base your remarks on draft
                    political directive, Deptel 4790,<note n="3" xml:id="d135fn3">
                        <ref target="#d82">Document 82</ref>.</note> and other pertinent telegrams.
                    If feasible you should also urge <persName corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName>
                    take necessary steps to prevent information being transmitted outside of Lebanon
                    prior actual landing.</p>
                <p>If for any reason task force should be unable make exact deadline, task force
                    commander being instructed communicate any time change to you.</p>
                <pb facs="0272" n="240" xml:id="pg_240"/>
                <p>Shortly before landings you should request Lebanese Government issue immediate
                    NOTAM closing Beirut Airport and, if considered necessary, declaring airspace
                    over Lebanon danger area until further notice.</p>
                <p>While we hope that US action will bring improvement general situation Lebanon,
                    assume you, in collaboration with appropriate military commander, will take such
                    further necessary evacuation action as local circumstances may require.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
